      field[trkMax].value += hp</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMPSGGArti" name="Artiste" description="The luminary may make a Perform check (for any kind of performance they wish) any time a Diplomacy check is called for, and may use Perform checks to pass secret messages as if making a Bluff check.\n\nThe luminary is a master of the arts, and can use their artistic skills to control social situations and convey meaning without making their communications obvious." compset="CustomSpec" summary="Use Perform instead of Diplomacy, and pass secret messages" uniqueness="unique">
    <comment>Anachronistic Adventurers - The Luminary

Super Genius Games
www.supergeniusgames.com</comment>
    <usesource source="MPRGGAnac"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="arMPSGGLum" name="Luminary" abbrev="Luminary"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="Secondary"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpMCH"/>
    <eval phase="Final" priority="20000"><![CDATA[#situational[hero.child[skDiplo], "You may use any Perform skill instead of Diplomacy.", field[thingname].text]

#situational[hero.child[skBluff], "You may use any Perform skill when passing secret messages instead of Bluff.", field[thingname].text]]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMPSGGAoCm" name="Aura of Calm" description="As a move action, the luminary is able to exude an aura of calm, putting other&apos;s at ease. Characters within 15 feet who can see and hear them can take 10 on skill checks, even when they would normally prevent them from doing so.\n\nAt 5th level, the luminary grants allies affected by her aura of calm a +1 bonus to skill checks when they take 10. This bonus increases by +1 every 4 levels thereafter. A luminary is aware that their aura of calm is an illusion, and does not benefit from their own aura.\n\nThe luminary&apos;s aura of calm lasts for one minute per luminary level, and they may use it a number of times per day equal to their Charisma bonus (Minimum of 1)." compset="CustomSpec" summary="As a move action, put others at ease with your aura" uniqueness="unique">
    <comment>Anachronistic Adventurers - The Luminary

Super Genius Games
www.supergeniusgames.com</comment>
    <usesource source="MPRGGAnac"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="arMPSGGLum" name="Luminary" abbrev="Luminary"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="Secondary"/>
    <tag group="ChargeAttr" tag="aCHA"/>
    <tag group="Usage" tag="Day"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="Tracker"/>
    <tag group="ChargeCalc" tag="FinalMin1"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpMCH"/>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="10000"><![CDATA[var auraBonus as number

auraBonus = field[xTotalLev].value

if (auraBonus >= 5) then
      auraBonus -= 5
      auraBonus = auraBonus/4
      auraBonus = round(auraBonus,0,-1) + 1
      field[livename].text = field[thingname].text & " (" & signed(auraBonus) & " Skill Bonus, " & field[xTotalLev].value & " minute duration)"
else
      field[livename].text = field[thingname].text & " (" & field[xTotalLev].value & " minute duration)"
endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMPSGGBegu" name="Beguiling" description="Once per day, if the luminary can talk to a target without significant interruption for five minutes or more they can attempt to convince the target they are a true and trustworthy friend. The target must make a Will save.\n\nDC 10 + 1/2 luminary&apos;s class level + luminary&apos;s Charisma modifier. If Failed, the target&apos;s attitude toward the luminary switchs to friendly for 24 hours.\n\nThe luminary can weave a web of charm and seduction so thorough that they can actually befuddle a target&apos;s better judgment and bring it under their influence. If the luminary takes any action that would normally cause the target of their beguiling to change its attitude regarding a creature it was friendly toward, the target receives a new saving throw against the beguiling effect. When determining what a beguiled creature will and won&apos;t do, the host may treat the ability as similar to the charm person spell.\n\nA luminary may only have one creature beguiled at a time. A luminary may attempt to keep the same creature beguiled for multiple days, but the target receives a cumulative +1 bonus to its saving throw for each day it is beguiled.\n\nBeguiling is a mind-affecting, language- dependent ability. A luminary must have taken the charming talent before they can take the beguiling talent." compset="CustomSpec" summary="Weave a web of charm and seduction" uniqueness="unique">
    <comment>Anachronistic Adventurers - The Luminary

Super Genius Games
www.supergeniusgames.com</comment>
    <fieldval field="trkMax" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="MPRGGAnac"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="Secondary"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="arMPSGGLum" name="Luminary" abbrev="Luminary"/>
    <tag group="Usage" tag="Day"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="Tracker"/>
    <tag group="abSave" tag="WillDis"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpMCH"/>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="10000"><![CDATA[var beguBonus as number

beguBonus = #levelcount[MSRDChari]/2
beguBonus = round(beguBonus,0,-1)
beguBonus += 10 + hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value

field[livename].text = field[thingname].text & " (DC " & beguBonus & " Will Save)"]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMPSGGCath" name="Catharsis" description="The luminary&apos;s force of personal magnetism increases to the point that, as a full-round action, they can arouse a single emotion of their choice in a target. A luminary may select two emotions when this talent is taken. \n\nOnce selected, these choices which they may instill in targets with the catharsis ability cannot be changed.\n\nA luminary may take this talent more than once. Each time they may select two additional emotions they can instill with catharsis, and gain an additional two uses per day of the talent.\n\nThe target must be able to see and hear the luminary. The target makes a Will save (DC 10 + 1/2 luminary&apos;s class level + luminary&apos;s Charisma modifier). (As with most saving throws, the target may choose to fail this save.) If the target succeeds at the saving throw, they are immune to the luminary&apos;s catharsis ability for 24 hours. If the target fails, they react with a single emotion of the luminary&apos;s choice as described below for 1d4 rounds, +1 round per 2 luminary levels, unless the specific emotion states otherwise.\n\nThis ability is language-dependent. A luminary may use catharsis a number of times per day equal to their Charisma bonus (minimum 1/day)." compset="CustomSpec" summary="Arouse a single emotion of her choice in a target">
    <comment>Anachronistic Adventurers - The Luminary

Super Genius Games
www.supergeniusgames.com</comment>
