  <thing id="cMPSGGFlou" name="Flourish" description="Whenever the luminary makes an attack roll they would normally be allowed to add their Dexterity modifier to, they may instead add their Charisma modifier.\n\nThe luminary has learned a combat style that takes advantage of their ability to make grand gestures and postures look noble and dashing rather than silly or overblown. When attacking with such flourishes, the luminary both makes attacks from unexpected angles and boosts their own self-confidence, making their attacks more accurate." compset="CustomSpec" summary="For Dexterity based attacks, replace with Charisma" uniqueness="unique">
