  <thing id="cMPSGGInsp" name="Inspired" description="The luminary can sometimes inspire themselves4 to achieve things that should by rights be beyond them. As a result, they may treat any ability score as a 13 when meeting feat prerequisites (even for non-bonus feats).\n\nThey may also select one of the following feats as a bonus feat, and must meet the feat&apos;s prerequisites. Acrobatic, Additional Traits*, Alertness, Animal Affinity, Athletic, Blind-Fight, Catch-Off Guard, Combat Expertise, Dodge, Fleet, Intimidating Prowess, Persuasive, Quick Draw, Run, Skill Focus, Stealthy.\n\nA luminary may select this talent more than once. Each time, they gain an additional bonus feat from the list, and may treat all their ability scores as being one higher than 13 for feat prerequisites (14 if selected twice, 15 if selected three times, and so on)." compset="CustomSpec" summary="Treat any ability score as a 13 for Feat Pre-reqs. Additional Bonus Feat">
