  <thing id="cMPSGGJeer" name="Jeer" description="The luminary can attempt to enrage a foe so it throws caution and tactics to the wind and attacks the luminary. They either take a full-round action to insult the target, or successfully hit them with an attack and choose to deal half damage.\n\nThe wound itself is an insult - often from the luminary carving their initials into the target. If insulting, the target must be able to hear and understand them. They attack even when other choices might be wiser.\n\nThe target of a jeer must make a Will save (DC 10 + 1/2 luminary&apos;s class level + luminary&apos;s Charisma modifier). On a failed save, the target is enraged at the luminary, and wants to harm them. Any round the target does not attack the luminary (using the definition of attack given in the invisibility spell), the target takes a penalty on all attack rolls, skill checks, concentration checks, and Will saving throws equal to the luminary&apos;s Charisma bonus (minimum -1). If it is not possible for the target to attack the luminary (if the target cannot see or reach the luminary,  for  example),  but the target takes at least a move action to attempt to change circumstances so it can attack the luminary on its next round (host&apos;s discretion), the target does not take penalties from the jeer ability.\n\nThe target remains affected for a number of rounds equal to 1d4 +1/2 the luminary&apos;s class level. A luminary may use jeer a number of times per day equal to 3 + their Charisma modifier." compset="CustomSpec" summary="The luminary can attempt to enrage a foe" uniqueness="unique">
