  <thing id="cMPSGGLIOf" name="Laugh It Off" description="As a standard action, the luminary can mock a specific action or attack taken by a foe, convincing the enemy to cease using a specific tactic. The luminary mocks the target&apos;s choice of tactic and the target must make a Will save.\n\nDC 10 +1/2 the luminary&apos;s class level + the luminary&apos;s Charisma modifier\n\nThey select a weapon, combat maneuver, spell, or extraordinary, spell-like or supernatural ability the target used in the past round. If successful they are convinced not to use the weapon, maneuver, or ability for 1d4 rounds. The target is free to use similar abilities or weapons; they are only restricted from using exactly the weapon, maneuver, or ability selected by the luminary.\n\nA luminary may use laugh it off a number of times per day equal to their Charisma bonus (minimum 1/day)." compset="CustomSpec" summary="Can mock a specific action or attack taken by a foe" uniqueness="unique">
